properties.name: Skydive Alabama
properties.description: Open Thursday through Sunday year round. Currently the only turbine DZ in Alabama. We own and operate a Cessna 208 Caravan. Rigging Services available during business hours.

properties.name: Alaska Skydive Center
properties.description: Open on weekends from the beginning of April to October. Weekdays are by appointment. From Anchorage, take Glenn Highway north; take Palmer exit to Inner Springer Loop after fairgrounds to Palmer Municipal Airport. Camping and RV spots are available next to airport. Cessna 206 drop zone.

properties.name: Phoenix Area Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week year round. We specialize in First time Tandem Jumps. From I-10, take exit 185 (AZ 387). Go south 3.6 miles and turn right on West Airport Road into Casa Grande Municipal Airport. Please call ahead for availability.

properties.name: Red Rock Skydiving, LLC
properties.description: Open 7 days a week by appointment. Beautiful Sedona Red Rock views. From Phoenix, take I-17 north. From Flagstaff, take I-17 south. From either city, take exit 287 and follow 260 west to Cottonwood. Take 89A south to Mingus Ave. and turn left. The DZ is the second airport entrance on the left. Indoor packing area.

properties.name: Skydive Arizona
properties.description: Largest fleet of skydiving aircraft: 4 Super Twin Otters, 5 Super Skyvans, Pilatus Porter, Hot Air Balloons & 14 foot Skyventure Wind Tunnel. World champion coaches and organizers. Pool, restaurant/bar, team rooms, bunkhouse, motel, rigging loft, gear store and indoor packing. 50 miles south of Phoenix off I-10.

properties.name: Skydive Phoenix
properties.description: Skydive Phoenix is located just 20 miles south of downtown Phoenix. Open 7 days a week year round. We pride ourselves in making your experience safe, fun, and memorable. We welcome all levels of jumpers, from first-timers to the experienced. We offer multiple disciplines of instruction, specializing in tandem student training.

properties.name: Skydive Skyranch
properties.description: Open Fridays and weekends featuring a carpeted packing area, pea gravel pit and 280 HP Cessna 182's. Twin Beech also available.

properties.name: Bay Area Skydiving
properties.description: At Bay Area Skydiving, we offer a fun and friendly, family-based DZ for all to enjoy. We are centrally located to the Bay Area, San Francisco, and the Central Valley. We vary in skydives from RW, freeflying, skysurfing and whatever else we can come up with. All are welcome! Open Wednesday through Sunday year round.

properties.name: Madera Parachute Center
properties.description: Open Saturday and Sunday. Huge on-airport landing area and grass or hangar packing areas. 10,500-ft. altitude with great view of Sierra Nevadas and San Joaquin Valley. Friendly, unpretentious, family atmosphere. Activities for non-jumpers close by (golf, theater and shopping). All skill levels welcome.

properties.name: Naval Postgraduate School Foundation Skydiving Club
properties.description: Military club skydiving out of Skydive Monterey Bay.

properties.name: NorCal Skydiving
properties.description: Located in California Wine Country at Cloverdale Airport. Views of the Alexander Valley, Pacific Ocean and Mount Shasta from 13000 feet. See www.norcalskydiving.com for reservations and directions.

properties.name: Pacific Coast Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week year-round. We are mostly a tandem drop zone. We have RVT video technology and scenic flights over the ocean before every jump. Located just 20 minutes from downtown San Diego.

properties.name: Santa Cruz Skydiving / Skydive Surf City
properties.description: Open six days a week, year round (closed Wednesdays). We are predominately a Tandem operation. Sport jumpers are only taken on a space available basis, so call in advance. Just off highway 1, 15 minutes south of Santa Cruz, exit: Freedom Airport Blvd.

properties.name: SkyDance SkyDiving
properties.description: Quality skydiving in Northern California. Home of the 30,000 ft. skydives and host to the Olympic Skydiving Team. Complete facilities and Pro Shop (Action Air Parachutes). Freeflying and formation coaching available. Open daily. Close to San Francisco, Napa Valley, Lake Tahoe and Sacramento.

properties.name: Skydive California
properties.description: Open five days a week, all year round. Located on our own private airstrip that is only one hour east of the San Francisco Bay Area. Air-conditioned packing area. Excellent coaching staff!

properties.name: Skydive Coastal California
properties.description: Tandem Skydiving only 40 minutes from Los Angeles. Beautiful Ocean views on a scenic flight to altitude and during 120 mph freefall. From Los Angeles take the 101 north to Camarillo exit 55 for Las Posas Road and turn left. Go 1 mile to Pleasent Valley Road and turn right. Go 1/2 mile to Airport Way and turn right. Go 1/4 mile to Durley Ave and turn left. Park at the Way Point Cafe on the right. We are in the camarillo Aircraft Service building to the left of the Cafe.

properties.name: Skydive Elsinore
properties.description: Open year round! One hour from San Diego and Los Angeles. Nestled in the scenic recreational valley of Lake Elsinore, CA. Beautiful lake and ocean views nestled in the surrounding San Bernadino and Ortega Mountains. FS, FF and WS organizing and coaching available. Covered packing and creeping areas. Known as one of the worlds friendliest drop-zone. Please feel free to contact us so that we can assist you in planning your stay.

properties.name: Skydive Hollister
properties.description: Open seven days a week year-round. From the Bay area, head south on U.S. Hwy. 101 to Gilroy. At the south end of Gilroy, take California 25 S. After about seven miles, take a left on Hwy. 156 N. After about one mile, take a right on San Felipe Road. After about one mile, turn right into Hollister Airport. Adventure Center Skydiving is located on your right. Full service Dropzone featuring AFF instruction, Tandem skydives and Rigging!

properties.name: Skydive Monterey Bay
properties.description: Open seven days, year round. King Air 200 series jumps to 15k & 18k. Ocean view. From San Francisco, take 101-south to hwy 156 W to Monterey Peninsula, then hwy 1 south to Reservation Rd exit, then left at Imjin Rd into Marina Municipal Airport, left on Neeson Rd. Coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive Perris
properties.description: Club Med of Skydiving! Wind tunnel on-site. Open 365 days a year. Free load organizing for all disciplines on weekends. Facilities include: fully equipped house, bar, and video rooms. Square One with full rigging services on DZ. 1.5 hour drive to LAX airport; beaches, mountains, amusement parks and Hollywood. A true family vacation combination!

properties.name: Skydive Sacramento
properties.description: Open Wednesday through Sunday. Take Freeway 80 to 65 North. Exit right onto Nelson. Turn left onto Nicolas Rd, then right onto Airport Rd.

properties.name: Skydive San Diego
properties.description: Come out and jump two twin otters over beautiful sunny San Diego. Views of the mountains, ocean and Mexico on every jump. Gear sales, food and coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive San Joaquin Valley
properties.description: Skydive San Joaquin Valley is located at DB Cooper Field about 75 miles north of Los Angeles. Check out our website for more details!

properties.name: Skydive Santa Barbara, LLC
properties.description: Open seven days a week. Check the website for directions. www.skydivesantabarbara.com Just 15 minutes from the ocean. 18,000 ft jumps available! Jumpers with less than 1000 jumps are required to use an AAD.

properties.name: Skydive Taft
properties.description: Open everyday except Wednesdays. One hour and 45 minutes north of L.A. Freefly and RW coaching available!

properties.name: Tsunami Skydivers
properties.description: Southern California's closest DZ to the Pacific Ocean. Skydive in the middle of Oceanside CA, 1 mile from the harbor and beach. PAC750XL flies Thursday thru Sunday and holiday Mondays. Located on Oceanside Municipal Airport just east of I-5 on hwy 76. B, C and D license holders and Tandem only. 760-390-JUMP

properties.name: Mile-Hi Skydiving Center, Inc.
properties.description: Nestled against the Rocky Mountains and less than 25 miles from the Denver metro area. Three new hangars complete with all modern facilities and indoor packing. All disciplines welcome. Boulder, a mecca for outdoor sports, is just a 15 minute drive. Open year-round on weekends and seven days a week spring through fall.

properties.name: Out Of The Blue Skydiving
properties.description: Located at the Fremont County Airport. We are less than an hour from both Colorado Springs and Pueblo. Our student services include tandem and AFF. Experienced jumpers also welcome. Full-time rigging loft.

properties.name: Skydive Colorado
properties.description: Open 5-7 days a week. Six miles from Canon City on Hwy 50. Come see the Royal Gorge and float the Arkansas River after your jump!

properties.name: Connecticut Parachutists, Inc.
properties.description: One of New England's premier skydiving centers. Open Thursday-Sunday April through October. Weekends only December through November. Freeflying, RW, CRW, Wingsuiting and accuracy. Covered packing areas, bonfire pit and great skydiving! Check out our website for featured events. Come learn, fun jump or take a tandem at CPI. Home of Champions.

properties.name: Skydive Danielson
location: 28 miles W of Providence, RI; 48 miles E of Hartford, CT
properties.description: Open 7 days a week, April-November. Tri-State border MA/CT/RI. I-395 exit 93. West on CT 101/Hartford Pike. Left on Upper Maple St. Right on Airport Rd.

properties.name: Skydive Delmarva, Inc.
properties.description: Open six days a week (Wednesday-Monday). Team rates, covered packing with TVs and VCRs, and covered creeping. Wide-open landing area. 30 minutes from Delaware and Maryland beaches. Easy access from Washington DC, Baltimore, Annapolis, Wilmington and Philadelphia.

properties.name: Florida Skydiving Center/Skydive Lake Wales
properties.description: We have 250 acres of wide-open landing area. Instruction is available to all levels of skydivers. Friendly staff. Please call for hours of operation. For summer hours please call first.

properties.name: Jump Florida Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. We have fun and friendly staff!

properties.name: Miami Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open 7 days a week 365 days a year. Take the turnpike south to SW 120th St. Turn right on 120th St. Turn left on 137th Ave. Turn right into Tamiami Airport and follow the signs to the Air Sal Building. We specialize in student training. Scenic flights over the ocean are included with most jumps. Enjoy views of the Miami skyline, Biscayne Bay, the Florida Keys and much more. Jumps are only a few miles from the ocean.

properties.name: School of Human Flight
properties.description: We serve Tallahassee, Panama City, Destin, Ft Walton, Dothan & Valdosta. Friendly family atmosphere. All disciplines are welcome. Beautiful sunsets. Memorable parties. Rigging services available on a drop off basis. Call ahead for scheduling.

properties.name: Skydive Amelia Island
properties.description: Open year round. Located 34 miles north of Jacksonville. Cessna tandem operation with great views!!

properties.name: Skydive City Zephyrhills
properties.description: Florida's Skydiving Resort. We have full amenities for your vacation and training. Food, laundry, camping, trailers for rent, rigging, gear sales, rating school, bar, internet access and much more. We also have RVs available for rent!

properties.name: Skydive DeLand Inc
properties.description: United Parachute Technologies (RWS) tandem examiners on site. Home of Skydive University. Facilities for teams, groups and individuals of all experience levels. Extensive parachute manufacturing support for all skydiving equipment. Fitness facilities on airport. The Perfect Spot Restaurant and Bar (full-service with video theater). Upgraded aircraft. Open full time 365 days per year.

properties.name: Skydive Jacksonville
properties.description: Open 7 days a week. Located 11 miles west of Jacksonville at Herlong Airport off of Normandy Blvd.

properties.name: Skydive Key West
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. Tandems only.

properties.name: Skydive Lakeside
location: 25 miles west of West Palm Beach
properties.description: Open Tues and Wed by appointment, Sat and Sun from 8am til sunset. 25 minutes west of West Palm Beach. All disciplines are welcome. Beautiful view of Lake Okeechobee!

properties.name: Skydive Miami
properties.description: Welcome to Skydive Miami. We are one of the closest full-service DZs to Miami, South Beach and Ft. Lauderdale. We offer great rates, so come jump with us out of our 15-place Turbine Caravan and enjoy our modern indoor air-conditioned facilities for a fantastic holiday. We look forward to seeing you at Skydive Miami.

properties.name: Skydive Palatka
properties.description: Skydive Palatka is near the St. Johns River. We have new facilities, including a training room and a large covered packing area. November activities include the annual Hog Flop Boogie.

properties.name: Skydive Palm Beach
properties.description: Located at Palm Beach County Glades Airport--just 25 miles west of West Palm Beach. 561-JumpNow or skydivepalmbeach.com

properties.name: Skydive Sebastian
properties.description: Skydiving over the Florida Coastline! Tandem Skydives, (AFF) Accelerated Freefall Student Courses, and "destination" or a "home" drop zone for Experienced Skydivers. RW, Freefly, CReW, and Canopy coaching available. Load organizing, Beach Jumps, Zoo Bar & Cafe. Located on the Florida Coastline allowing visiting skydivers to enjoy an the view of the Sebastian Inlet and the Atlantic Ocean while in freefall and under canopy as well as a coastal environment after skydiving.

properties.name: Skydive Space Center
properties.description: 30 minutes from Orlando. Take 528 E to 95 N to Exit 220. East on Garden St. 1.3 miles, turn left onto Williams Ave. Open seven days a week.

properties.name: Skydive Spaceland-Clewiston
location: 50 miles W of West Palm Beach
properties.description: Within one hour driving distance from West Palm Beach, Ft Lauderdale and Ft Myers. Within one and a half hours from Miami and Naples. Beautiful views of Lake Okeechobee. Large hangar for packing. Large FBO terminal with hot shower.

properties.name: SkydiveLive!
properties.description: Open Saturday, Sunday and military/holiday 4-day weekends. 60 miles northeast of Panama City, FL. Spend the weekend! 5000sqf indoor packing/sleeping area, RV hookups, 20 acre landing area with 100's of acres of "outs". Cessna 182 and PAC750 in the winter. All disciplines with coaching, inexpensive military transitions. VERY family friendly!

properties.name: SW Florida Skydive Club
properties.description: Open five days a week. Seven miles east of Punta Gorda. I-75 exit 164, north on US-17. Turn right onto Washington Loop Road. 2500 square feet carpeted hangar.

properties.name: World Skydiving Center Florida
properties.description: Scenic Florida DZ on a 130 acre private airport! Huge indoor packing hanger. Camping allowed. Located between Jacksonville and Tallahasee. Easy access between Interstate 10 and Interstate 75. Fly in with your own plane! Identifier FD63.

properties.name: Skydive Atlanta
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday and Sunday year-round. Full-service DZ. Located just off I-75, one hour from Atlanta, Macon, and Columbus. Large, open landing areas. First-class facility in a 15,000-sq.-ft. hangar with loft, indoor packing, creeping space, and several TVs for video review. Only 20-ft. walk to loading area. Professional, friendly staff.

properties.name: Skydive Georgia
properties.description: Open seven days a week. One hour northwest of Atlanta. Our facilities offer free bunk room, wireless internet and of course air conditioned and carpeted packing area.

properties.name: Skydive The Farm
properties.description: Skydive The Farm is situated on a beautiful 55- acre private farm. The landing area is spectacular, with flat, green grass and two natural swoop ponds. The hangar is new, and the facility is world class. Top it off with great vibes and great people. You have a true skydiving resort.

properties.name: The Jumping Place
properties.description: Currently open every weekend. Will open during the week if you have 4 jumpers willing to commit to 8 jumps or more. From Savannah(I95), take 16 West to exit 127. At exit 127, go NW on State Rd 67 for 10.8 miles. Turn right on US 301 bypass for 4.5 miles. Turn right onto Airport Blvd. In 1/2 mile, turn right onto Airport Dr. We are in the large hangar on your left. Blue hangar with large The Jumping Place sign. Large hangar with 900 acres to land on! Call 912-322-7282 for the gate access code.

properties.name: Pacific Skydiving Center
properties.description: 2 new, fast Supervan 900 Grand Caravans with 950 HP. We fly jumpers and students to 14000 ft guaranteed. Member of the Better Business Bureau with A+ rating. Safety is our number one priority. Our beautiful drop zone is open 364 days a year. Closed only on Christmas day. We have an international staff, coaching, great jump planes, A/C in all rooms, top of the line equipment, services and value. Jump in paradise! Check out our website: www.pacificskydivinghawaii.com

properties.name: Sky Down Skydiving
properties.description: Open 365 days a year. A friendly, yet professional environment where safety always comes first. Huge facility with easy I-84 access. 2500 foot indoor climate controlled packing room. Large grass landing area for experienced jumpers. Multiple landing areas to accommodate all skill levels. Breathtaking view of Lake Lowell, Boise valley, the Snake River and Owyhee Mountains. Come jump with us for one of the most scenic views in Idaho!

properties.name: Skydive Idaho
properties.description: Owned and operated by world record holders and USPA Nationals medalist. Skydive Idaho operates on a private runway covering 150 acres of scenic landscape and grass parachute landing area. We also have two covered picnic areas for your parties and/or events. Visit the dropzone where our fun, safe, and professional staff won't treat you like a number. All skill levels welcome. Wingsuit School and Freefly Instruction also available. Jump with the best!

properties.name: Snake River Skydiving
properties.description: Open weekends by appointment. Only 10 minutes from the Perrine Bridge. From Twin Falls, go south on Blue Lakes and follow the signs to the airport down Shoshone Street when you get to "5 Points". Shoshone will take you straight to the airport. Air-conditioned packing and manifest area. Swooping and CRW friendly. Jump with the best!

properties.name: Chicagoland Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open seven days a week. Home of the "Sweet Fleet". Some of the nicest super otter and PAC 750XLs in skydiving.

properties.name: Illinois Skydiving Center
properties.description: Weekdays by appointment. 8:00am - Sunset during weekends. Located 4 miles southeast of Rantoul on a private airstrip. No airport hassles. Larger aircraft for special events.

properties.name: Illinois Valley Parachute Club
properties.description: Open weekends 10:00am until dark. Tuesday and Thursday 4:00pm until dark during daylight saving. From Bloomington take Rte 9 west to Rte 122 west. Turn left just three miles west of Minier. From Peoria take I-74 east to I-155 south to Rte 122 east. Turn right three miles east of Hopedale on Mackinaw Road.

properties.name: SEMO Skydiving
properties.description: Small friendly DZ, open weekends year round. Indoor packing and spacious landing area. Located 30 miles southeast of Cape Girardeau, MO just off I-57.

properties.name: Skydive Chicago Inc
properties.description: The midwest's largest skydiving resort. From the Chicago area, I-55 south to I-80W, Exit 93, 71 north to Dayton Road and turn right. Host of the 2016 World Championships. Home of the 138-way Vertical World Record. Open 7 days a week. RW and freefly coaching. Indoor packing, team rooms, bar & restaurant, and Disc Golf! Some of the fastest aircraft in the midwest.

properties.name: Skydive Greater
properties.description: Open weekends only. 30 miles south of Chicago. Exit 308 on I57 to 60 south then 1.5 miles to Airport Road West. Personalized tandem instruction, relaxed atmosphere, restricted access, excellent hangar and facilities. Weekdays by appointment only.

properties.name: Air Indiana Skydiving Center, LLC
properties.description: Open weekends. From Lafayette, take Hwy 26 east to Hwy 39. Go north to Hwy Division Road, then west 2 miles to County Road 800 west. Cross 800 west and airport is 1/8 mile on the left.

properties.name: Gravity Powered Sports LLC
properties.description: Open 5 days a week, Wednesday through Sunday. Located 2 miles west of I-69 (Angola exit). Indoor packing in hangar. We fly a Cessna 182 that's in great condition! Camping available across the road. Video and still shot pictures available too. Tandem, AFF and IAD classes offered. And don't forget your memorabilia from your wonderful experience!

properties.name: Jerry's Skydiving Circus
properties.description: Open Easter-Thanksgiving; Thursday and Friday afternoons, and Saturday and Sunday from 10am to dark. Tandems by appointment. Inside carpeted packing area.

properties.name: Plymouth Sky Sports
properties.description: Open seven days a week early April through early November. Take US-30 to US-17, Go North 2500 feet. Airport is on the right. Coaching available, turbine aircraft on regular schedule (see website event calendar).

properties.name: Skydive Greater Michigan City
properties.description: Tandem Skydiving! Open 7 days a week, April-November. 62 driving and 40 nautical miles from downtown Chicago. Great views of the Chicago skyline and minutes from Michigan City beaches and outlet malls. Skydive Greater Michigan City and Kankakee, Il locations focus on Tandem Skydiving and Training, to ensure customer satisfaction.

properties.name: Skydive Indianapolis
properties.description: Open seven days a week, March 1-November 15. From Indianapolis go I-65 north (25 min) to exit 158. Go east two miles to Frankfort Airport. Coaching available.

properties.name: Des Moines Skydivers, LLC
properties.description: Only 15 minutes from I-35 and I-80. Open weekends and some weekdays--call the dropzone for jumping information. Full facilities including camping, showers, A/C and heated hangar, gear rental and student as well as experienced jumper training. Only club owned and operated DZ in Iowa. Turbine aircraft available June-September. Home of the Couch Freaks.

properties.name: Paradise Skydives
properties.description: Open weekends April to November.

properties.name: Air Capital Drop Zone
properties.description: Open weekends March through December. A fun, safe little Kansas DZ. Located only 10 minutes SE of Wichita, or 15 minutes from Downtown. We do quite a few tandems through the summer months, but typically only every 2nd or 3rd load with our Super 182--15 minutes to 10K!

properties.name: Kansas State University Parachute Club
properties.description: Located near the great college town of Manhattan, KSUPC is one of the oldest collegiate parachute clubs in existence. Open weekends and some weekdays all year long. First-jump courses are scheduled regularly, and visitors are welcome. Carpeted packing.

properties.name: Skydive Kansas
location: 30 miles S of Topeka; 30 miles W of Ottawa; 35 miles NE of Emporia
properties.description: From Topeka, take 75 S to 31 W. Open weekends year-round and some weekdays during the summer. (Call first during winter months) Large carpeted indoor packing area. Nice lounge area with heat, A/C and hot shower. Family-oriented DZ with kid play area and concessions. Offering training for student skydivers, coaches, tandem instructors, examiners and riggers.

properties.name: Jumping For Fun, LLC
properties.description: Small airport with relaxed atmosphere. We have a lot of experience and are willing to work with students or challenge an experienced jumper.

properties.name: Skydive Kentucky
properties.description: Open Saturdays & Sundays year round. During daylight savings time; Monday, Wednesday, and Friday afternoons--1 pm to dusk. From Louisville, take I-65 S to exit 91. Then exit 136. Turn left at 2nd light (St. John Rd/1357) Turn left at next light (Ring Rd/3005). 50 yards turn on to Kitty Hawk Dr. Please park

properties.name: Skydive Nawlins.com
properties.description: Open Wednesday thru Sunday year round. From New Orleans, take I-10 east to exit 267B. Take I-12 west to Exit 80. Turn right on Airport Road. Coaching available in all disciplines.

properties.name: Jump And Raft
properties.description: Jump and Raft is a small friendly place for tandems, fun jumpers and students, in the heart of the Maine Wilderness with stunning views. Mountains, lakes and wilderness provide a setting that makes every jump extra special. Full onsite amenities including camping, lodging, bar and restaurant. The Home of Serious FUN!

properties.name: Skydive New England
properties.description: Open seven days a week from April to November. Flying a Super Otter, Cessna 206 and Cessna 182. On-site camping, private airport, bunkhouses, showers/bathrooms, covered packing, video rooms and on-site restaurant. Offering tandem and AFF training as well as FF and RW organizing. The only swoop pond in New England!

properties.name: Vacationland Skydiving
properties.description: Open Thur-Sun and by appointment throughout the summer. 30 miles south of Bangor at Pittsfield Municipal Airport.

properties.name: Ocean City Skydiving Center
properties.description: The only beach front skydiving center serving metro DC, Baltimore and all of Delmarva. OC Skydiving Center provides tandem first jump and tandem progression training only.

properties.name: Jumptown/MSPC, Inc.
properties.description: Open Thursday-Sunday, and holidays (April-November). Club atmosphere with elected board of directors. Home of the Massachusetts Sport Parachute, and UMASS Parachute Club. Indoor and shaded packing areas. All levels of student and experienced jumpers welcome. Route 2 west, exit 16. Brand new state of the art hangar, offices, lounge and much more for the 2014 season.

properties.name: Pepperell Skydiving Center
properties.description: Close to Boston and easy to reach from any New England metro area. New England Boogie with Skyvan every August. Free load organizers every weekend. Take Rt 3 to Exit 5W (Rt 111 West) in Nashua, N.H. Go west 5 miles to Pepperell Airport on the left. Only 15 minutes from the SkyVenture New Hampshire wind tunnel. Parachute shop and master rigger on airport. Open til October 31st.

properties.name: Skydive Barnstable
properties.description: Open seven days a week, May thru October. Tandem-only operation.

properties.name: Skydive South Boston
properties.description: Open 6 days a week, April through September. Located 45 miles south of Boston.

properties.name: Capital City Skydiving
location: 20 miles E of Lansing; 35 miles NW of Ann Arbor
properties.description: We are a small, fun, Cessna Drop Zone. Open Thursday-Sunday with other weekdays by appointment. Fun jumpers welcome but call prior to arrival. We have a large grass landing area for students and fun jumpers. We are located in Fowlerville only minutes from I-96. Check our website for directions.

properties.name: Midwest Freefall Sport Parachute Club, Inc.
properties.description: A fun, casual DZ with a country atmosphere and nice turbine aircraft. Only a few miles from metro Detroit. Located just southeast of Romeo, Michigan, on the Kunstman Airfield at 29 Mile and Kunstman Rd. USPA membership required. Check website for hours and special events.

properties.name: Napoleon Skydiving Center
properties.description: We have AFF evaluators and tandem examiners (Relative Workshop) on staff, and senior and master riggers available. Store, restaurant, and lounge next to the airport. Open six days a week, May-October. Weather permitting, we are open weekends the remainder of the year.

properties.name: Skydive Allegan
properties.description: We are headquartered in Allegan Michigan and offer a full range of skydiving services. We offer first-time tandem skydives, complete student skydiving training, and lots of fun jumps for experienced, licensed skydivers. We are now located less than an hour away from Grand Rapids, Lansing, Battle Creek, Kalamazoo and the Michigan lakeshore. Come see what all the excitement is all about!

properties.name: Skydive Harbor Springs
properties.description: Jump in beautiful Northern Michigan. Only a mile from the shoreline. Fun jumpers welcome. Great views and scenic sights with every jump. We specialize in first time tandem jumps.

properties.name: Skydive Hastings 3.0
properties.description: Closest drop zone to Grand Rapids. Wingsuit sales and instruction available. Beginners welcome!

properties.name: Skydive Michigan!, Inc.
properties.description: Open seven days a week April-October; 9am to sunset. Skydive Michigan!, Inc. caters to all levels of skydiving and particularly to students just graduating from student status. Most jumpers are family-oriented individuals and come out for good, clean fun!

properties.name: Skydive Owosso
properties.description: Open April-October. Our Cessna 182 is available to fly 7 days a week. We specialize in Tandem skydiving, AFF, and Wingsuit first flights. Coaching available for Relative Work, Wingsuit, and Free Fly disciplines. 30 miles east of Lansing and 20 miles west of Flint.

properties.name: Skydive Tecumseh
properties.description: Open April - October. Super fast Blackhawk Grand Caravan. Friendly atmosphere. Close to Detroit, Ann Arbor and Toledo. We are less than an hour from Detroit or Toledo. Indoor packing, load organziers, coaching, and wide open landing area with separate high performance area.

properties.name: Wild Wind Skydivers
properties.description: Located just two miles off I-75 Expressway, east of Saginaw, Michigan. Progressive AFF-based school and coaching program leading to A license. Student training available seven days a week, weather permitting. Integrated with on-airport tandem and IAD operations.

properties.name: Minnesota Skydivers Club, Inc.
properties.description: Open weekends April to October. Static line and tandem training with gear rental. Take I-35 south of Minneapolis to 14 west to Waseca Airport. The airport is located two miles southwest of town.

properties.name: Skydive Adventures
properties.description: Open Saturdays and Sundays, year-round. From Sioux Falls, take I-90 East to Hwy. 75 (Luverne, Minn. Exit). Go one mile south to Quentin Aanenson Airport. Heated hangar.

properties.name: Skydive Minnesota
properties.description: Family oriented Cessna DZ located 55 minutes north of Minneapolis. Just off hwy 169 at the south end of the Milaca Municipal Airport. Tandem, AFF, Gear Rental, Video and Rigging services available, as well as Coaching for RW and Freeflying. Open seven days a week, May-Oct. www.skydiveminnesota.org Phone 763-913-4497

properties.name: Skydive Twin Cities Forest Lake
location: Daniel A DePonti / Forest Lake Airport (25D)
properties.description: Less than 30 minute drive from the Twin Cities, Take I-35 north to MN-97, go east on MN-97 for 1.8 miles and south on Forest Road N to the Forest Lake Airport. Open May-October, 7 days a week. Indoor packing available.

properties.name: Southern Minnesota Skydiving
properties.description: Open 3 days a week; Friday, Saturday, Sunday and by appointment during the weekdays. From Twin Cities go south on I35. Take a right on highway 14 in Owatonna. Left on 110th Street in Waseca. The airport is on the right. Coaching, SL and Tandem Instruction and Rigging services available.

properties.name: Westside Skydivers
properties.description: Open seven days a week from April 1st to November 30th. Come jump over lake Winsted and see the beautiful views of Lake Minnetonka.

properties.name: Gold Coast Skydivers
location: I H Bass Jr Memorial Airport (4R1)
properties.description: Open year-round, Gold Coast Skydivers is known for its relaxed, jumper-friendly atmosphere. Free coaching for all skydiving disciplines. Our close proximity to New Orleans make Gold Coast the place to jump on the Gulf Coast. Original home of the Pink Mafia.

properties.name: Ozarks Skydive Center

Located halfway between Springfield and Joplin; 12 miles north of Exit 38 on I-44 (2 miles north of Hwy 96) on Hwy 97, north to Lawrence County 2040. East 3/4 mile to drop zone.

properties.name: Skydive Kansas City, Inc

properties.name: Meadow Peak Skydiving

We host the annual Lost Prairie Boogie, August 3-11 2013, and all student services are provided by Skydive Lost Prairie across the Carson Field Airport runway (MT53).

properties.name: Crete Skydiving Center, Inc.
properties.description: Open Saturdays and Sundays plus Fridays during Daylight Savings Time. An easy drive from Lincoln, Omaha, or Grand Island. 2000 square foot carpeted packing area, wide-open landing area and wireless internet access. Noted for friendly atmosphere.

properties.name: Lincoln Sport Parachute Club

properties.description: From Weeping Water, we are located one mile east of the end of Eldora Ave. Open weekends year-round and Wednesday during Daylight Savings Time. We have an air conditioned and heated packing area. True club atmosphere.

properties.name: Nebraska Skydiving School
properties.description: Open four days a week (Fri-Mon). From Omaha, head west on I-80. Take Exit 257 (Holdrege exit). 8 miles south on Highway 183.

properties.name: Sin City Skydiving
properties.description: Specializing in first-time jumpers. Sin City Skydiving is the best value in the Las Vegas area!

properties.name: Skydive Las Vegas
properties.description: Welcome to Las Vegas' premier student skydiving center specializing in student tandem training. We fly a new Pacific Aerospace P-750 XSTOL (PAC-750XL), utilize the newest state-of-the-art equipment, and offer complimentary transportation from the Las Vegas Strip in our luxury passenger vans. Enjoy spectacular views of Hoover Dam, Lake Mead and the Las Vegas Strip as your friends and family watch you land right next to our facility. Your experience at Skydive Las Vegas will be second-to-none! Open 7 days a week 365 days a year. Visit us at www.skydivelasvegas.com or on Facebook at www.facebook.com/skydivelasvegas.

properties.name: Skydive Mesquite

Freefly, Wingsuit or RW, all welcome. If you want to fun jump near Las Vegas, this is the place to be.

properties.name: Vegas Extreme Skydiving Inc.

properties.description: Home of Champions! Open seven days a week. One of the Northeast's top team training centers with coaching for all disciplines, including wingsuit coaching! Rating courses, Sisters in Skydiving, state of the art student training and master riggers.

properties.name: Skydive East Coast
properties.description: Open 7 days a week from March to November. Parking and internet access available. We are off of exit 58 of the Garden State Parkway. Only 20 minutes from Atlantic City and 10 minutes from LBI. Easy access from Philly using the AC Expressway.

properties.name: Skydive Jersey
location: 63 miles W of New York City

properties.name: Skydive El Paso

We fly two Cessna 182's, have an excellent group of staff & instructors providing AFF, IAD, Static Line and Tandem coaching and a nice family RV Park, hotels and restaurants just minutes away.

properties.name: 516 Skydive, Inc

properties.description: Minutes away from scenic Lake George, NY. Family oriented DZ. Open April - November 7 days a week by appointment; weekend winter hours by appointment as well. I-87 to exit 20, north on Route 9 for 1/2 mile then right on Rt 149 for 9.3 miles. Brand new hangar, indoor packing area, scenic helicopter flights, ultralights, and flight training also available. A complete aviation fun park!

properties.name: Blue Sky Ranch

properties.name: Finger Lakes Skydivers

Cook-outs on Saturdays. No hook turns please.

properties.name: Frontier Skydivers

The dropzone is located 15 miles from Niagara Falls, 20 miles from Buffalo and St. Catherines and 50 miles from Rochester. Also within driving distance of Toronto, Hamilton and Erie, PA.

properties.name: Long Island Skydiving Center

Take William Floyd Pkwy South 2.7 miles to Hwy 27 East (Sunrise Hwy East) to Exit 61. Go South two miles to Montauk Hwy (Hwy 80). Turn left onto Montauk Hwy and go East for 1/2 mile to Spadaro Airport on the left. Enjoy beautiful views of Long Island's Atlantic coastline and Hampton Beaches.

properties.name: Mohawk Valley Skydiving
properties.description: Open Wednesday through Friday afternoons; Saturdays, Sundays, and holidays, sunrise to sunset (also by appointment) mid-March through mid-November. Located three minutes from New York State Thruway Exit 26 on New York State Rte. 5.

properties.name: Rochester Skydivers
properties.description: Quiet country setting with very low air traffic. Beaches and lake within 15 miles of drop zone. Indoor packing with air-conditioning and heat. Indoor restrooms and kitchen area. Paved and lighted runway. Located 30 minutes east of Buffalo and 30 minutes west of Rochester. Take Rte. 104 to 98 South to Barre Center, Maple St. to Pine Hill Rd. The dropzone is located on Pine Hill Airport.

properties.name: Skydive Long Island
location: 70 miles E of New York City
properties.description: Skydive Long Island is a full-service drop zone flying to 13,500 ft. with a Grand Caravan off a 10,000-foot runway. Large landing area. An hour from New York City and ten minutes from the famous â€œHamptons.â€ Exit 69 off the Long Island Expressway. The view is magnificent, with the Atlantic Ocean, Long Island Sound, and the Peconic Bay. Freefly coaching and load organizers.

properties.name: Skydive South Shore
location: 50 miles E of New York City
properties.description: Open seven days per week, seasonally April through November. From New York City, take the Long Island Expressway (LIE) east to Exit 68. Take William Floyd Pkwy south 2.2 miles to Dawn Dr. Turn left onto Dawn Dr. Go .5 miles to 135 Dawn Dr. Skydive South Shore is on the left in the main terminal building of the Brookhaven-Calabro Airport. Enjoy beautiful views of Long Island's world-renowned North and South Shores along with the Atlantic coastline and Hampton Beaches.

properties.name: Skydive The Ranch

properties.name: Adrenaline Air Sports/Carolina Skydiving

properties.name: East Carolina Skydiving
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday and Sunday year round. 25 miles NE of Greenville, NC. Camping area, hot showers, indoor packing, gear sales and rental.

properties.name: Skydive Coastal Carolinas

Southport and Oak Island also offer a variety of activities along with lodging and restaurant within two miles. Regular beach jumps enjoyed at sunset.

properties.name: Skydive Little Washington, LLC
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday, and Sunday year-round. Air-conditioned and heated packing area. Call or visit our website for further details.

properties.name: Skydive OBX
properties.description: Open April-November. Located at the Dare County Regional Airport in Manteo. Call or visit our website for detailed directions. Located on a barrier island and where powered flight all began. Experience a scenic jump over the beautiful Outer Banks of NC. We specialize in Tandem jumps.

properties.name: Skydive Paraclete XP
properties.description: Open year round, 7 days a week, sunrise to sunset at PK Airpark in Raeford, NC. PAC 750, 2 Caravans and a Twin Otter available. Swoop pond, enclosed packing, and full-service bar and grill. Convenient to Fayetteville, Raleigh, and Southern Pines. Five minutes from Paraclete XP SkyVenture Indoor Skydiving!

properties.name: Triangle Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open Wednesday through Sunday year round. Fast place; 10 minutes to altitude, large landing area with separate high performance area. RW and FF load organizers/coaches/videographers. Indoor packing with thick rubber mats for comfort. Upstairs classrooms for professional training environment and a rigging loft with a rigger on site. 20 minute drive north of Raleigh.

properties.name: US Army Parachute Team (Golden Knights)
properties.description: The Golden Knights are one of the most winning parachute teams in the world! The winning tradition spans over 50 years in which the team has produced 408 national and 66 world champions. To learn more about joining a winning team, check our web site or call 1-800-USA-ARMY.

properties.name: Skydive Fargo!, Inc.
properties.description: Skydive Fargo is located six miles west of Fargo's Hectar Airport. Open weekends and evenings May - October, weather permitting. We own a 182 with a 300-hp engine and offer pleasant hangar facilities.

properties.name: Aerohio Skydiving Center
location: Corner State Route 604 and Blough Rd.
properties.description: Our DZ offers a small DZ atmosphere with large DZ facilities and staff. The DZ is located near I-71 and I-76, making us one of the closest to the Akron, Cleveland and Columbus areas. Open four days a week, Thursday through Sunday. *Please call ahead for weekday jumps.

properties.name: Alliance Sport Parachute Club / Skydive Rick's
properties.description: Small, friendly atmosphere, 45 minutes west of Pittsburgh International Airport. Club in existence for 53 years. Aircraft very well maintained. Open landing area. Open Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday evenings. Open all day Saturday, Sunday, and holidays. Open weekends year-round. Heated packing and creeping area.

properties.name: Canton Air Sports
properties.description: Open seven days a week March through November. Swooping pond, bonfire parties, free camping, and hot showers. Four miles north of Alliance, OH on state route 225 (Union Ave).

properties.name: Cleveland Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open Friday-Monday. Take 480E to 422E. Go south on Rt 88 for 1.5 miles then go straight onto Grove Rd for 1 mile.

properties.name: Jump Ohio

properties.name: Ohio Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open primarily on weekends March-November with occasional jumping during the week. Friendly family atmosphere located in the center of Ohio.

properties.name: Start Skydiving

Open seven days a week. Visit our website for more info.

properties.name: Oklahoma Skydiving Center
location: 60 miles NE of Oklahoma City/ 40 miles SW of Tulsa
properties.description: Open 7 days a week by appointment. On-site rigging services, carpeted packing area, air conditioned lobby and classroom. Coaching available.

Last hanger on south end of airport.

properties.name: Eugene Skydivers

We boast the friendliest atmosphere on I-5 and welcome all levels of experience. Warning: Jumpers who visit often never leave. Pack extra boxers.

properties.name: Pacific Northwest Skydiving Center

Open from 10:00am-Sunset 7 days a week from October 1-May 1; weather permitting. Summer hours: 9:00am-Sunset 7 days a week from May 1-October 1.

properties.name: Skydive Oregon, Inc.

Enjoy our fast 850 HP turbine aircraft throughout the jump season as well as 65-acres of grass landing area, an air-conditioned/heated clubhouse, shaded packing decks, wireless internet, adjacent camping area and spectacular mountain views. Nearby swimming, kayaking, skiing and climbing.

properties.name: Above It All Skydiving School / Skydive Philadelphia
properties.description: One of Philadelphia's busiest full-service turbine drop zones. Open seven days a week March-November. We offer indoor packing, creeping space, and all the amenities you would expect from an industry-leading skydiving provider.

properties.name: Above the Poconos Skydivers / NEPA Ripcords Inc
location: Old Milnesville Rd. and Hess Rd.
90 miles W of New York City

Open weekends year round. Thursday and Friday after work by appointment May thru October. Operated by Guinness Record Holder '92-present.

properties.name: Chambersburg Skydiving Center, Inc.

State College activities, entertainment and nightlife a half-hour away.

properties.name: Skydive Pennsylvania

Free camping. Exit 113 off I-79, take 208 W one mile. Make a right at Old Ash Road. Skydive Pennsylvania is 1/2 mile on the right.

RW and Advanced Freefly (AFP) coaching available. Organizing every weekend. Team rates available.

properties.name: Boston Skydive Center

properties.name: Skydive Walterboro, Inc.

properties.name: South Carolina Skydiving

properties.name: Adventure Skydiving Tennessee

properties.name: Chattanooga Skydiving Company

Swoop pond, shower facilities, camping on DZ, gear rental, climate controlled indoor packing, training room, video room, wireless internet, packers, freefall camera flyers for hire. Less than two miles off of Interstate 40 at Exit 412, follow blue interstate signage to DZ entrance on W Dumplin Valley Rd.

properties.name: Skydive Tennessee
properties.description: Closest drop zone to Nashville. Open Thursday through Sunday year round. Cessna Grand Caravan. Minutes from restaurants and hotels.

properties.name: Dallas Skydive Center

Dallas Skydive Center is the home of Forest McBride and his legendary "Air Forest One"--the fastest Cessna 182 in the country! We'll take you to 13,500 feet in less than 18 minutes! DSC is a good-vibe DZ that welcomes all disciplines.

properties.name: Lone Star Parachute Center

properties.name: Skydive SPI

properties.name: Ogden Skydiving Center

properties.name: Skydive Utah

properties.description: Open five days a week except during the winter time. 20 minutes west of SLC International Airport. See our website for directions More directions.

properties.name: Malone Parachute Club
properties.description: Open select weekends April - October. Check out the calendar on www.maloneparachuteclub.com. 45 minutes from Burlington, VT & 45 minues from Montreal, Quebec. Family-oriented, not-for-profit drop zone with 41 years of operation.

properties.name: Vermont Skydiving Adventures, Inc.
properties.description: Open four days a week. Closed Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays.

properties.name: DC Skydiving Center

properties.name: No Limits Skydiving West Point

properties.name: Skydive Orange, Inc.

properties.name: Virginia Skydiving Center

properties.name: Jet City Skydiving

properties.name: Skydive Snohomish, Inc.
properties.description: A welcoming atmosphere, convenient location, excellent equipment, and breathtaking scenery are what make Snohomish, an exceptional skydive training and recreation center. Visit our website and see for yourself the 360-degree scenic landscape, aircraft (turbine and souped-up piston-power), first-class facilities, hours of operation and detailed driving directions.

properties.name: Skydive Toledo
properties.description: Friendly drop zone located between Portland, Oregon and Olympia, Wash. View of Mt. St. Helens and Cascade mountain range. Open year-round. AFF and Coach Examiner on site. All jumpers welcome!

properties.name: West Plains Skydiving -The Ritz-
properties.description: Open Friday-Monday and Wednesdays April-November, occasionally weeknights. From Spokane, travel west on I-90 to exit #226 and drive 1/4 mile on Schoessler Rd. Indoor packing.

properties.name: Great Lakes Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week March-November. Indoor packing. Tandem and Coach Examiners and rigger on staff. 2 miles from Exit 1 off I-39-I90.

properties.name: Green Bay Skydivers
properties.description: State Hwy. 29 (Shawano Avenue) from Green Bay, northwest ten miles to State Hwy. 32, north five miles to Carter Pulaski Airport, east on Airport Drive to hangar. Open Wednesday and Friday 4pm - dark from Memorial Day through Labor Day and weekends year round (weather dependent).

properties.name: Seven Hills Skydivers of Madison, WI
properties.description: Located approximately 15 minutes north of Madison on a rural, picturesque airport. Friendly, non-profit club owned and operated. Established in 1962. Large, comfortable clubhouse with indoor heated and air-conditioned packing area. Great camping and picnic areas on the DZ. Open Wednesday afternoons in summer (4-sunset) and weekends (9-sunset) year round (weather providing).

properties.name: Skydive Adventure
properties.description: The DZ is open year round: May through September-seven days a week; October through April-weekends, weather permitting and weekdays by appointment. Indoor heated packing area, vending machines, and a picnic area with grills. Open landing area with a great view of lakes, woods, and the city on descent. We are a student operation, but welcome visiting jumpers at our drug-free drop zone. We look forward to your visit and hope you stick around after jumping for a social evening.

properties.name: Skydive Midwest
location: 50 miles N of Chicago, 30 miles S of Milwaukee
properties.description: Open seven days a week. April-November. We offer tandem, AFF and welcome experienced skydiver. From Chicago take I-94 north to Exit 335, turn left. When you reach South Sylvania Ave. turn right. From Milwaukee take I-94 south to Exit 333 turn right on Hwy 20 then left on S Sylvania.

properties.name: Skydive Milwaukee/Sky Knights Sport Parachute Club
properties.description: Open seven days a week April-October and weekends in the winter. Closed-in packing area. Heated and air-conditioned office, classrooms and video area. Two-story lounge and theater with observation deck. Large grill available for cookouts. Lots of grass and landing area with swoop course for all skydiving needs.

properties.name: Skydive Superior
properties.description: Under new management! Located at the top of Wisconsin on the very tip of the largest fresh water lake (Superior) in the world! Family owned and operated, Skydive Superior offers breathtaking views and friendly people. Brand new state-of-the-art hangar with new training, packing and lounge areas. Camping available. Open year round and New Years Eve jumps available. R-44 Helicopter and Turbine Aircraft also available. Celebrating our 55th year. We are one of America's oldest drop zones!

properties.name: Skydive Twin Cities
properties.description: Weekdays 10:00am until sunset. Weekends 8:00am until sunset. From Twin Cities take I-94 E. into Wisconsin to Exit 16 or the Hammond Exit. Go north 1.5 miles to County Rd. J. Go east two miles, the airport is on the north side of County Rd. J. Indoor packing available. Super Grand Caravan available during summer season.

properties.name: Skydive Wissota/Indianhead SPC
properties.description: Open weekends year-round and Wednesday evenings during Daylight Savings Time. Located near Lake Wissota and State Park. Air-conditioned and heated club house.

properties.name: Wisconsin Skydiving Center
properties.description: Located at Fort Atkinson Municipal Airport along the scenic Rock River. Beautiful new facilities. Indoor packing. Fast-climbing 182s (12,500 ft. in twenty minutes). AFF examiner, tandem examiner, and master rigger on staff. Thirty-five years of experience. Safe, fun skydiving. Enjoy no politics! Relaxed AtmospAIR!

properties.name: World Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open seven days a week from April 15th to October 15th. From Chicago, take 94 North the Exit 342. Turn East of Rt 158(52nd St) for one mile to Kenosha Regional Airport.

properties.name: Skydive Virgin Islands
properties.description: Open seven days a week, December-April 1st. Skydive Virgin Islands is the only skydiving center in the Virgin Islands. Please call 340-2773925 for reservations, directions, and operation schedule.
